@DESCRIPTION: Whenever a customer purchases a product/service he has a perception about the value he will receive out of it. During the time he is consuming the services, the customer is bound to evaluate value and confirm the perception or change it.

There are times when the customer would have interruptions in regular working of his service and would be interacting with the CSP, via either of the channels available for him, to diagnose the service for better or proper functioning.

If the diagnosis has not resulted in a resolution, the customer will be raising a request or a ticket with the CSP to request help for resolution. These interactions are considered part of the request to resolve sub phase of the customer's journey.

The CSP will be reaching out to the customer at periodic times to notify him/her about his/her balance and a payment request notification. The notification can also be post the payment has been received by the customer confirming the same.

Change name to Service Catalog Management 
Updated Overview

Workforce Management

This contribution should be a L1 in the Resource X Operations Support & Readiness and should replace the Workforce Management L2 under Resource Process Management.
Upon receiving a notification the customer will verify the charges applied to his subscription. This could be confirmed by him or alternatively, he/she may dispute the charges with the CSP.

The Topup/Pay sub phase of the lifecycle is when the customer is making payment for the services he has availed or in some cases, paying in advance for charges he is going to avail to the CSP. The Topup/Pay interactions could be via a variety of modes and channels depending upon what is available for him/her.
Enhance selection - During the renew phase of the lifecycle, the customer will be making changes to his service and selection based on his/her past experience or others experiences.

Once the selection has been confirmed by the customer, he/she will recontract the services/products with the CSP for a subsequent tenure. This could be dependent upon the kind of service and payment type selected by the customer.

Depending upon his/her personal experience the customer is bound to refer the CSP positively or negatively to his circle of inluence. Considering the impact of social media in our lives today, this is a critical part of the customer's lifecycle which should be understood and managed by CSP's.

Depending upon the tenure and/or revenue contribution to a CSP the customer will gain loyalty with a CSP. The loyalty could either be in monetary terms or in non-monetary terms (such as preferential queues in stores etc.)

When a customer makes a decision to leave a service provider, he/she will usually explicitly or implicity provide feedback. The feedback can be usually captured at various phases and interactions with the customer, however this specific sub phase is usually entaining at the time of termination of the service.
The discontinue subphase confirms the cancellation of the service and subscription of the customer with the CSP.

Process Name (L2): Charging
Brief Description: Managing the assignment of a value (monetary or other) to an
event or product, or combination (bundle or aggregate) of the above.
Extended Description: The purpose of Charging is to assign a value (monetary or other) to an event or product, or combination (bundle or aggregate) of the above. The charge may be either a credit or a debit. 
The processes involved in assigning a value (charging) and application of the value to a balance include rating, application of discounts, and aggregation.
Rating processes are responsible for calculating the assigned value by multiplying some quantity of items by a price. These processes can be as simple as a price multiplied by a quantity of one or may involve more complex calculations using accumulations or aggregations of items. Prices may be expressed as monetary or other units of measure. Prices are established through mechanisms such as contracts, tariffs, service agreements or price lists. Prices may be affected by the application of discounts.
The values resulting from rating and the application of discounts can then be applied to a customer's balance. The balance affected by the value may be monetary or other balances such as minutes, points, or tokens.
Rating and application of discounts may occur in real-time, near real-time, or may be executed on a periodic basis. These processes will also support pre-paid and post-paid pricing arrangements. 
The charge may appear on a customer invoice via Apply Pricing, Discounting, Adjustments & Rebates.

This could be explicit step in the customers journey wherein he/she has initiatied interaction with the CSP to get details of the product and/or service in relation to him receiving it.

The customer during the reserve sub phase is requesting the CSP to hold the inventory (most likely the physical inventory). The reservation in this case is prior to the actual formal selection and order submission step as at this time he is still evaluating the product and wanting to get an actual demonstration or viewing before he/she confirms.
The select product/service confirms the customers selection on the offering from the CSP.

As part of the choosing phase, the customer will then place the order with the CSP. The Place Order step includes the components of providing information for verification of the customers identity, making initial payment as needed; including deposit.

The next phase in the lifecycle for the customer is around receiving the product/service he has selected. Depending upon the type of service this could be right at the time of the selection (i.e. in the case of wireless) or could be a separate step once some backend function/operation is completed.

The use phase of the lifecycle is where the customer has the most amount of interaction with the CSP. A lot of the experience of the customer is built around the usability and consumption of the services.

Based on the usage, the customer will review his/her usage. This could be post the use phase by viewing his transactions or during the use phase itself as he is implicitly observing the usage of his product/service with the CSP
